In honor of Mental Health Awareness Month, here’s a reminder to always take care of your mental health & well-being… We never know what someone is going through behind the scenes, so a little bit of kindness & compassion goes a long way🥰🙏🏽 We’re not weak for being vulnerable. We’re not selfish for taking time for ourselves. We’re not soft for needing to rest. We are human😌Let’s continue to speak up about mental health & end the stigma around it 🤜🏽🤛🏽We all struggle at times, so let’s show more empathy & compassion towards ourselves & others!🫶🏽💕 Also, if anyone is ever in need of a hug, I’ve been told I give good hugs! 😁🤗 #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth #MentalHealthAwarenessWeek #MentalHealthMatters #EndTheStigma #YouAreNotAlone

I hit my first squash ball a couple days ago. It’s been 6 weeks post surgery. When I did my left Achilles in 2017, I chose not to step on court for 4.5 months. I had no interest. I was burnt out & told myself I didn’t want to play until I could move. Now, I can barely move, but I wanted to get on court. Nobody told me to go hit. Nobody told me to train. Nobody told me how long I needed to be on court. I showed up to @kineticracquet because I’m happier when I move my body. I chose to get on court because I felt like hitting some balls. I hit for 10 min & that was it. The next day, I did it again. I hit because being on court makes me happy these days. I have an unbelievably long way to go, but for now, this feels like a WIN☺️🤩💪🏽 #JustWontQuit
